# The Ladybird-engine browser bundle (/lib/ladybird) is NOT baked into the base
# image — it ships in the signed herald package "lantern" (engine .so closure +
# the /apps/lantern launcher). The trusted-path anchor for /lib/ladybird is now
# DYNAMIC: herald appends it to /etc/aegis/anchors on install (from the package's
# paths= line) and calls sys_install_commit, after which the kernel both grants
# policy caps to and write-protects the tree. No baked-in placeholder dir is
# needed (the old static s_ladybird_ino mount-time anchor is gone).

